Diffusion MRI sequence artifacts were removed using the Anima toolbox by performing the following step: (a) Eddy current correction and motion correction: it is performed by registering each sub-volume of the CUSP data linearly then non-linearly to the first sub-volume. Each non-linear transformation is computed only in the phase encoding direction; (b) Distortion correction: It is designed to register two \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
